3️⃣ describe, context, it
🔹 describe

Used to group tests for a class or method.

RSpec.describe User do

Means: “We are writing tests for User”.

🔹 context

Used to describe a scenario.

context "when name is present" do

Think of it as:

Under this condition...

🔹 it

Defines a test case.

it "is valid" do

Means:

It should behave like this.

So structure becomes:

RSpec.describe User do
  context "when name is present" do
    it "is valid" do
      ...
    end
  end
end

Very readable — almost English.